    dt_i/ds = +2 * sum_{j!=i} 1/(t_i - t_j)
This is the REPULSIVE pairwise flow:
- neighbouring points spread apart as s increases
- isolated-pair law is sep(s) = sqrt(sep0^2 + 8 s)
